# Pre-Build Checklist — Attendance Management System

## 1. API Keys & Credentials — Get these first

These are blockers. Without them, the dashboard widgets won't work.

| Service           | Where to get it                                             | Free tier?            |
|-------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|-----------------------|
| **Google OAuth**  | https://console.cloud.google.com → Credentials → OAuth 2.0  | ✅ Free               |
| **NewsAPI**       | https://newsapi.org → Register                              | ✅ Free (100 req/day) |
| **Alpha Vantage** | https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key → Get free key | ✅ Free (25 req/day)  |
| **Open-Meteo**    | No key needed                                               | ✅ Fully free         |

> **Action:** Register for these now and keep the keys handy for the `.env` file.

---

## 2. Dev Machine — Install Checks

Run each command to verify the tool is installed:

| Tool                        | Purpose                     | Check command      |
|-----------------------------|-----------------------------|--------------------|
| **Java 11+**                | Run Clojure / backend       | `java -version`    |
| **Leiningen**               | Clojure build tool          | `lein --version`   |
| **Node.js 18+**             | Required by Shadow-cljs     | `node --version`   |
| **Docker + Docker Compose** | Run the full stack          | `docker --version` |
| **PostgreSQL client**       | Optional, for DB inspection | `psql --version`   |

> **Action:** Install any missing tools before starting the build.

---

## 3. Project Location

Decide where the project directory should be created:

- [ ] Inside current directory: `dummy/attendance-system/`
- [ ] Alongside current directory: `MuggleBornPadawan/attendance-system/`

---

## 4. Google OAuth — Redirect URI

Set the following **Authorized Redirect URI** in Google Cloud Console:

- **Local dev:** `http://localhost:3000/auth/google/callback`
- **Production:** `http://<your-server-ip-or-domain>/auth/google/callback`

> **Action:** Decide your production URL/IP now so it can be configured from the start.

---

## 5. Office Geofence Coordinates

The GPS check-in feature requires the office location.

- [ ] Office latitude: ___________
- [ ] Office longitude: ___________
- [ ] Allowed radius (meters): ___________ *(suggested: 100–200m)*

> Tip: Find coordinates via Google Maps (right-click on your office location → "What's here?")
> These can also be configured later via the Admin Panel UI.

---

## 6. First Admin User

Since employees self-register via Google OAuth, one account must be pre-seeded as admin.

- [ ] Admin Google account email: ___________

> This email will be inserted into the database seed script with the `admin` role and `active` status.

---

## 7. Project Naming

Affects directory name, Clojure namespaces, and Docker image names.

- [ ] Project directory name: ___________ *(e.g., `attendance-system`)*
- [ ] Clojure namespace prefix: ___________ *(e.g., `com.mycompany.attendance`)*

---

## 8. Leave Policy Defaults

Default annual leave entitlements seeded into the database:

| Leave Type   | Suggested Default | Your Value |
|--------------|-------------------|------------|
| Sick Leave   | 10 days/year      | ___        |
| Casual Leave | 12 days/year      | ___        |
| Paid Leave   | 15 days/year      | ___        |

> These are global defaults. Admin can override per employee via the Admin Panel.

---

## Summary — What to Do Now

1. ✅ Run the dev tool checks (`java`, `lein`, `node`, `docker`)
2. ✅ Register for API keys (Google OAuth + NewsAPI + Alpha Vantage)
3. ✅ Fill in the blanks in sections 3–8 above
4. ✅ Share the answers and give the go-ahead to start building
